<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fire 75, Mystics 58  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   PORTLAND, Ore. (AP) -- Sophia Witherspoon scored 26 points to
lead the Portland Fire to a 75-58 victory over the Washington
Mystics on Sunday night.
</P>
<P>
   Sylvia Crawley added 17 points for the Fire (5-12), who trailed
most of the first half.
</P>
<P>
   Chamique Holdsclaw had 15 points and 12 rebounds to lead the
Mystics (8-10), while Nikki McCray scored 14 points.
</P>
<P>
   A 3-pointer by Tully Bevilaqua started the Fire on a 27-9 run
that gave them a 56-39 lead with 10:18 remaining as the Mystics did
not make a field goal for a span of 6:47.
</P>
<P>
   Holdsclaw then scored seven straight points, including a
3-pointer, to cut the lead to 10.
</P>
<P>
   But Witherspoon made a layup to end Portland's 2:44 scoring
drought, and Michelle Marciniak's two steals helped the Fire
increase the lead to 69-49 on DeMya Walker's layup with 4:45 left.
</P>
<P>
   Crawley picked up her third foul and sat down midway through the
first half, and the Mystics took the lead with 5:09 left when
Markita Aldridge hit a deep 3-pointer, starting an 8-2 run as
Washington took a 29-27 halftime lead.
</P>
<P>
   Forward Alisa Burras of Portland sprained her right knee in the
first half and did not return.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
