<BODY>
<HEADLINE> US Beats Canada 5-4 in Holiday Cup  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ALAMITOS, Calif. (AP) -- Brenda Villa scored with 2:37 left
as the U.S. women's water polo team beat Canada 5-4 on Sunday to
finish the Holiday Cup tournament 6-0.
</P>
<P>
   ''We worked hard to get to this point, but we still have a long
way to go before September,'' said U.S. coach Guy Baker, referring
to the Sydney Olympics.
</P>
<P>
   Canada's Johanne Begin tied it at 4 with 4:33 left.
</P>
<P>
   Nicolie Payne, who had 13 saves for the United States, was
selected the tournament's most valuable goalkeeper. Teammate
Coralie Simmons was honored as the most valuable offensive player,
and Canada's Cora Campbell was selected the top defensive player.
</P>
<P>
   Canada finished the tournament 4-2.
</P>
</TEXT>
