<HEADLINE> Dow Is Up 7; Nasdaq Slips 23  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks were mixed today as investors mulled the
impact of a slowing economy: steadier interest rates but the
potential for weaker corporate profits.
</P>
<P>
   At midmorning on Wall Street, The Dow Jones industrial average
was up 7.78 at 10,643.76, while the Nasdaq composite index was off
23.90 at 3,999.30.
</P>
<P>
   The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 index was down 1.67 at 1,477.23.
</P>
<P>
   Investors were trading cautiously today as they digested a
positive jobs report from the government on Friday. The report gave
the latest evidence that the U.S. economy is slowing in response to
the Federal Reserve's six interest rate increases since last June.
</P>
<P>
   Most economists now expect the Fed to leave rates unchanged for
the next few months. While that's good news for investors who were
unnerved earlier this year by the Fed's actions, there is still a
great deal of concern in the market that the cumulative effect of
the rate hikes will be a drop in corporate profits.
</P>
<P>
   Investors are also nervously awaiting the flood of second
quarter earnings reports, which start this week.
</P>
<P>
   ''Everybody is kind of waiting and watching until corporate
earnings announcements hit full stride the end of this week,'' said
Alan Ackerman, senior vice president at Fahnestock &AMP; Co.
</P>
<P>
   A pleasant surprise came this morning from aluminum producer
Alcoa, whose earnings came in higher than expected. Alcoa rose
$2.375 to $30.
</P>
<P>
   Yahoo!, expected to release its earnings report on Tuesday, fell
$4.313 to $113.375.
</P>
<P>
   Prudential Securities upgraded its rating on several retailers,
including Best Buy, up $2.06 to $73.56 and Circuit City Stores, up
$3.063 to $38.063.
</P>
<P>
   Lehman Brothers upgraded chip maker Applied MicroDevices, which
rose $3.375 to $85.375.
</P>
<P>
   Advancing issues outnumbered decliners by a narrow margin on the
New York Stock Exchange, where volume came to 239.45 million
shares, down from Monday's pace.
</P>
<P>
   The Russell 2000 index rose 0.83 to 529.05.
</P>
<P>
