<HEADLINE> Blinks, Flim Flam Lead US Dressage  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   GLADSTONE, N.J. (AP) -- Sue Blinks of Mount Kisco, N.Y., led the
U.S. dressage team for the Sydney Olympics announced Monday.
</P>
<P>
   Blinks, on Flim Flam, scored the highest on trials held in
Florida in May and in competitions in Europe in June.
</P>
<P>
   She was joined on the Olympic team by Christine Traurig of
Carlsbad, Calif., on Etienne; Guenter Seidel of Del Mar, Calif., on
Foltaire; and Robert Dover of Flemington, N.J., on Ranier. The
alternate is Kathleen Raine of Laguna Hills, Calif., on Fidelia.
</P>
<P>
   Seidel and Dover are veterans of the U.S. team that won the
bronze medal at the 1996 Olympics, and Dover has been on every U.S.
Olympic dressage team since 1984.
</P>
