<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Annan Says Africa Fuels Wars  </HEADLINE>
By AMBA DADSON
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOME, Togo (AP) -- Rich in diamonds and oil, Africa is being
plundered of raw materials that fuel wars and are ''now the source
of all our misery,'' U.N. Secretary General Kofi Annan said Monday.
</P>
<P>
   In an impassioned speech at the opening of an Organization of
African Unity Summit in Togo's capital, Annan handed out blame and
praise to the world's poorest continent -- the only region, he said,
where ''conflicts are not decreasing.''
</P>
<P>
   Annan, who is from Ghana, also reserved harsh criticism for the
so-called ''global economy,'' which he said cared little for the
welfare of Africans and was only interested in the continent's
abundant natural resources.
</P>
<P>
   Civil wars in Sierra Leone, Angola and Congo were spurred in
part by rebels' trade in diamonds that eventually end up in Western
markets.
</P>
<P>
   These riches, ''instead of being exploited for the benefit of
the people, have been so mismanaged and plundered that they are now
the source of our misery,'' Annan said.
</P>
<P>
   Yet he added that Africans bear much of the responsibility for
the deterioration of the continent's security and the withdrawal of
foreign aid.
</P>
<P>
   ''This is not something others have done to us,'' Annan said.
''It is something we have done to ourselves. If Africa is being
bypassed, it is because not enough of us are investing in policies
which would promote development and preserve peace,'' Annan said.
</P>
<P>
   Young people in Africa see their countries going backward, he
said, citing a litany of the continent's ills.
</P>
<P>
   --Africa has almost half of the world's refugees and internally
displaced people.
</P>
<P>
   --It is the world's poorest continent and sits at the bottom of
the U.N.'s Human Development Report on quality of life.
</P>
<P>
   --Africa has 33 of the world's 48 least developed countries.
</P>
<P>
   Annan also called on Africans to forge stronger economic and
security links similar to the European Union. He proposed that
Africans could similarly unite through an ''African Oil and Diamond
Community'' to administer resources that are the ''sinews of war.''
</P>
<P>
   Yet the Secretary-General also noted ''hopeful stories'' that he
said should inspire Africans and outsiders including AIDS reduction
in Senegal and Uganda, and flourishing democracies in many African
countries.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-07-10-00 1824 </TRAILER>
