<HEADLINE> Agent's Bond Hearing Postponed  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   COLUMBIA, S.C. (AP) -- A federal court bond hearing for sports
agent William ''Tank'' Black was postponed a week.
</P>
<P>
   Black, who said through his lawyer that he is innocent, was
indicted last week on money laundering and drug charges by a grand
jury in Detroit.
</P>
<P>
   The sports agent, wearing a suit along with handcuffs and
shackles, told U.S. Magistrate Judge Joseph McCrorey on Monday that
he wanted to continue the hearing for another week. His attorney,
John Hardaway, said the defense needed more time to prepare.
</P>
<P>
   Co-defendant Linda Wilson, Black's business partner, also
requested the continuance.
</P>
<P>
   Wilson operated World Express Travel Inc., a Columbia travel
agency which Black was chairman and chief executive.
</P>
<P>
   Prosecutors said Black hid drug dealers' money, moved drugs and
helped dealers hide out of the country. He is accused of laundering
$1.1 million and funneling it into a car title loan business.
</P>
<P>
   Black and Wilson also are charged with conspiracy and perjury.
Federal prosecutors say they plan to extradite the pair, who could
face as long as life in prison and $4 million in fines if convicted
of all counts.
</P>
<P>
   In another Florida case also pending trial, Black and others are
accused of stealing more than $5 million from about a dozen NFL
players. Black had been free on a $1 million bond in that case
before his latest arrest.
</P>
</TEXT>
