<HEADLINE> Nicastro Hired As Villanova AD  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   VILLANOVA, Pa. (AP) -- Vince Nicastro, Villanova's associate
athletic director for administration, was hired Monday as the
university's new athletic director.
</P>
<P>
   Nicastro, 34, replaces Tim Hofferth, who resigned last month to
run a sports marketing company.
</P>
<P>
   Nicastro has worked in the athletic department since 1994, when
he became Villanova's director of ticket operations. He was
promoted to assistant athletic director in 1997, before he moved up
shortly after to associate athletic director.
</P>
<P>
   Villanova has 550 athletes competing in 24 men's and women's
varsity sports.
</P>
