<HEADLINE> Skins Sign 3d Round Pick Harrison  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   ASHBURN, Va. (AP) -- Third-round draft pick Lloyd Harrison signed
a four-year, $1.714 million contract with the Washington Redskins
on Monday.
</P>
<P>
   Harrison, a cornerback from N.C. State, is expected to
contribute on special teams this season. He'll have a hard time
seeing playing time in a secondary stocked with Deion Sanders,
Darrell Green, and Champ Bailey.
</P>
<P>
   Harrison's deal includes a $503,000 signing bonus and can be
voided after the first three years.
</P>
<P>
   LaVar Arrington and Chris Samuels, the Nos. 2 and 3 overall
selections in the draft, still have not signed with Washington, nor
has sixth-round pick Todd Husak.
