<HEADLINE> Fire's Burras Suffers Injury  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   PORTLAND, Ore. (AP) -- Portland reserve forward Alisa Burras will
miss at least the next two games after spraining her right knee in
the Fire's victory over the Washington Mystics on Sunday night.
</P>
<P>
   Burras will not travel with the team on their road trip to Los
Angeles and Utah. She is scheduled to have an MRI exam Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   Burras has played in all 17 of the expansion Fire's games,
averaging 8.6 points and 4.1 rebounds. She leads the WNBA in
field-goal percentage at .612.
</P>
<P>
   The Fire are 5-12, the fourth-worst record in the WNBA, but have
won four of their last nine games.
</P>
</TEXT>
