<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-10 22:49 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 3 Thought Dead in Submerged Truck  </HEADLINE>
By MARK THIESSEN
<TEXT>
<P>
   COUNCIL BLUFFS, Iowa (AP) -- An adult and two children were
presumed dead Monday after the truck they were in plunged into the
Missouri River at a local park.
</P>
<P>
   ''I heard kids screaming. The truck went under so fast,'' said
Jeremy Johnston, 22, who was standing on a dock about 25 feet away
when the truck entered the river.
</P>
<P>
   The truck jumped off a 25-foot river bank Monday evening at
Narrows County Park, directly across the river from Omaha, Neb.'s
Eppley Airfield.
</P>
<P>
   Witnesses said it did not appear that the adult driver made any
effort to stop the vehicle, which sped off an access road about 100
feet from the river.
</P>
<P>
   ''It didn't try to swerve, no brake lights, nothing,'' said
Conrad Santon, 26, who also saw the truck from the dock. ''I heard
the engine rev up when they got close to the bank. It was insane.''
</P>
<P>
   Divers searched for the vehicle in 24 feet of water, battling
currents strong enough to pull off their face masks.
</P>
<P>
   ''It's a big struggle down there,'' said Council Bluffs Fire
Chief Alan Byers, who added authorities believe the vehicle's
occupants were an adult and two children.
</P>
<P>
   Rescue workers in boats and on the river's banks frantically
searched for the vehicle for more than two hours before the rescue
effort was called off. Authorities then focused on recovering the
bodies of the vehicle's occupants.
</P>
<P>
   A U.S. Coast Guard cutter was being used to drag the river's
bottom.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-07-10-00 2249 </TRAILER>
