<HEADLINE> Sol 59, Storm 42  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MIAMI (AP) -- Marlies Askamp had a season-high 21 points and 13
rebounds to lead the Miami Sol to a 59-42 victory over the fellow
expansion Seattle Storm on Monday night.
</P>
<P>
   Askamp, who shot 4-for-6 from the field and 13-for-18 from the
free-throw line, was Miami's only player in double figures.
</P>
<P>
   Stacey Lovelace was the only Seattle player in double figures
with 11 points in 14 minutes as a reserve.
</P>
<P>
   Miami (7-12) failed to reach 60 points for the 15th time this
season. The Sol, who entered the game last in the WNBA in scoring
and field-goal percentage, shot just 24 percent from the field
(10-for-41). They went 1-for-6 from 3-point range, but did convert
38-of-55 foul shots.
</P>
<P>
   Seattle (3-16), next to last in scoring and field-goal
percentage, has lost 11 of 12 games and scored below 60 points in
five of its last seven. The Storm finished at 30 percent from the
floor (13-for-43) and 1-for-8 from 3-point range.
</P>
<P>
   Miami led just 18-17 at halftime.
</P>
</TEXT>
