<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-10 23:21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nicaraguan Quake Toll Rises to 7  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MANAGUA, Nicaragua (AP) -- The death toll from a string of
earthquakes has risen to seven, while more than 35 people have been
reported injured, the country's civil defense said Monday.
</P>
<P>
   The quakes followed Thursday's magnitude 5.9 quake, which killed
four people and was centered 30 miles west of the capital, Managua.
A magnitude 5.2 temblor on Friday killed a 4-year-old boy and two
others, who died when their homes collapsed.
</P>
<P>
   The quakes destroyed 600 homes and partially damaged 1,900
others, officials said.
</P>
<P>
   Hundreds of families have refused to return to their homes,
fearing more quakes, and 13,071 people have taken refuge in 11
shelters.
</P>
<P>
   Damaged houses have been marked with white flags, and
authorities have begun demolishing those at risk of collapsing.
</P>
</TEXT>
